1 inhi bit operations of the facility, the person shall, upon
2 conviction, be guilty of a felony punishable by a fine of not less
3 more than Ten Thousand Dollars ($10,000.00), or by imprisonment in
4 the custody of the Department of Corrections for a term of one (1)
5 year, or by both such fine and imprisonment. As used in this
6 subsection, "loiter" means standing or waiting around idly or
7 without apparent or rational purpose.
8 B. Any person who shall willfully damage, destroy, vandalize,
9 deface or tamper with equipment in a critical infrastructure
10 facility shall, upon conviction, be guilty of a felony punishable by
11 a fine of One Hundred Thousand Dollars ($100,000.00), or by
12 imprisonment in the custody of the Department of Corrections for a
13 term of not more than ten (10) years, or by both such fine and
14 imprisonment.
15 C. If an organization is found to be a conspirator with persons
16 who are found to have committed any of the crimes described in
17 subsection A or B of this section, the conspiring organization shall
18 be punished by a fine that is ten times the amount of said fine
19 authorized by the appropriate provision of this section.
20 D. As used in this section, "critical infrastructure facility"
21 means:
